               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo / DD</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1889" notAfter="1913"> King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (r. <date>1872–89</date>), his son Rās <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2012Arayas">ʾArʾaya Śǝllāse Yoḥannǝs</persName> and 
                        King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> (r. <date>1889–1913</date>) are mentioned in supplication formulas throughout the manuscript. <ref target="#h1">Hand 1</ref> intersperses the names of the two kings and the rās in supplication formulas.
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> is mentioned on e.g., <locus target="#13ra #32 #33 #90vc24"/> <locus target="#15ra">15ra, ll 6–7</locus> <locus target="#43vc">43vc, ll 9–10</locus>.  
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2012Arayas">ʾArʾaya Śǝllāse Yoḥannǝs</persName> is mentioned on <locus target="#43rb #109vb #140va"/>. 
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> is mentioned on e.g., <locus target="#62r">62r, ll 9–10</locus>, <locus target="#90vc"/>, <locus from="16" to="17"/>. 
                        <ref target="#h2">Hand 2</ref> initially mentions <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName>, while the name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> appears only from <locus target="#183va"/>.
                        Most likely, <ref target="#h2">Hand 2</ref> started  writing the manuscript at the time of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> and finished during the reign of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName>.
                        To consult <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2375Synaxa#SecondHalf">Sǝnkǝssār (General record): Second half of the year</title> written by the same scribe, refer to <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd025">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi, DD-025</ref>. 
                     </origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance><persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14753WaldaGiyorgis">Walda Giyorgis</persName> is mentioned in the supplication formulas filled in by <ref target="#h1">Hand 1</ref> (in several cases his name was washed out).
                     Besides him, on <locus target="#25rc">25rc, ll 5–7</locus>, within the supplication formula at the end of the commemorative note, the names of several other individuals are mentioned as his wife and children, respectively:
                     <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14754RomanaWarq">Romāna Warq</persName>, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14755GabraMasqal">Gabra Masqal</persName> and <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14756GabraMaryam">Gabra Māryām</persName>. 
                     The name of the scribe <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14757WaldaMikael">Walda Mikāʾel</persName> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">daqiqa māḫbar</foreign> ‘children of the community’, that is, the Dabra Dāmmo monks are mentioned in the supplication formulas filled in by <ref target="#h2">Hand 2</ref> . 
                     In some supplication formulas on <locus from="3ra" to="105vc"/> the names of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14758TaklaMikael">Takla Mikāʾel</persName> e.g., <locus target="#6rb #7rb4"/>, <locus from="15" to="16"/>;
                     <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14759GabraEgzi">Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer</persName> e.g., <locus target="#50rb3 #50rb14 #76vc12"/>; <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14771GabraMikael">Gabra Mikāʾel</persName> <locus target="#43va"/>; <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14772NasaraAb">Naṣara ʾAb</persName> <locus target="#47ra #50rb"/>; 
                     <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14773WaldaMalak">Walda Malʾāk</persName><locus target="#47ra"/>; <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14774GabraMadhen">Gabra Madḫǝn</persName> <locus target="#76va"/> were added later by 
                     <ref type="hand" target="h3">Hand 3</ref> in place of the original names that were washed out or in blank spaces left for the name of a supplicant. Also, the name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I</persName> is entered into some of the supplication formulas beginning from <locus target="#51rb"/>.
                  </provenance>
               </history>
